-- ===================================================================== --
--  Module state: the reusable poll/status buffers
-- ===================================================================== --

-- Reusable raw buffers for the fill-a-buffer FFI (allocated via the verified
-- engine <builtin> MCMemoryAllocate; an LCB Data does not bridge to a void*).
-- Each pairs a Pointer with its current byte capacity. They persist for the
-- process - bounded reuse, the single-thread playbook - because there is no
-- deterministic library-unload hook to free them at (plan section 4.2).
variable sDrainPtr as Pointer
variable sDrainCap as Integer
variable sStatusPtr as Pointer
variable sStatusCap as Integer
variable sScratchPtr as Pointer
variable sScratchCap as Integer

-- ===================================================================== --
--  Foreign handlers (one per btx_* symbol in btx_abi.h). Buffer params are
--  `Pointer` - we hand them MCMemoryAllocate blocks (output) or MCDataGetBytePtr
--  pointers (input), never a Data value; short strings are ZStringUTF8;
--  64-bit values ride as ZStringUTF8. All cdecl. Never rename these binds.
-- ===================================================================== --

